title: 2025 Q1 Marin County Homelessness Executive Communications

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All emails between Paul Fordham of Homeward Bound and Gary Naja Reise between January 1st, 2025 to April 9th, 2025.

All emails between Amy Cunningham of the City of Novato and Gary Naja Reise between January 1st, 2025 to April 9th, 2025.

All emails between Heather Abrams of the Town of Fairfax  and Gary Naja Reise between January 1st, 2025 to April 9th, 2025.

All emails between Cristine Alilovich of the City of San Rafael  and Gary Naja Reise between January 1st, 2025 to April 9th, 2025.

All emails between Brad Gross or James Malcolm of the Richardson Bay Regional Agency  and Gary Naja Reise between January 1st, 2025 to April 9th, 2025.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robbie Powelson

title: Disability Pride Parade Permits 2018 - 2024 (Department of Cultural Affairs and Special Events)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

All applications/ permits submitted (Approved, Pending, or Denied) for the Disability Pride Parade from 2018 through 2024.
The event is typically the 3rd or 4th Saturday of July each year.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Zeke Martin
